                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18001203-78-off416 t18001203-78-crimeloc418"></join>, they are <rs id="t18001203-78-viclabel419" type="occupation">linen-drapers</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18001203-78-victim499 t18001203-78-viclabel419"></join>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18001203-78-victim500 t18001203-78-viclabel419"></join>: Last Friday, about half past four. I stood with my back to the door, and there were two chairs, with pieces of print on them, two or three paces in the shop; I accidentally turned my head, and saw the prisoner had them grasped in his hand, and skulking out of the shop door; I called, holloa, and he dropped the prints, and ran away, and I after him; he had got them off, and then dropped them; I pursued him, he run about ten or a dozen yard's, and then dropped into a walk; I took him back, and am confident he is the same man.</p>

               <p>Prisoner. He took hold of me, there were two men running, and, says he to me, I believe you are one; no, says I, I am not of that description, I am a seasaring man; says he, I shall take care of you.</p>
               <p>GEORGE LONGDEN sworn. - I took him into custody; I have seen him before; he is in the habit of being in very bad company.</p>
               <p>
